      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "GEE YOUNG (1) was responsible for a very good effort last time over 2120m at Dubbo, finishing second and just a head from the winner. Has the benefit of a good draw. Won't find this any harder and he can grab a win. LLANFAIR ROCKY (2) was out of the money two starts ago then things went wrong last start when he copped a check, broke, and finished a long last over 1730m at Bathurst. Likely to get all the favours this time from this nice draw. Meets a similar line up so he is sure to be a force with even luck. JUSTAQUICKSCHOONER (3) finished 35 metres back in sixth over 1660m at this track recently at his first race start. Strips fitter and can improve. TENACITY RED (6) could only manage seventh when resuming over 1660m at this track last start. Can do better.",
